  • Method Details

    • getNextGraph

      public DynamicGraph getNextGraph(int speed, boolean moveRandomly, boolean moveVelocity) throws IOException, NodeSuperimpositionException
      Outputs a Dynamic graph using the information from the next line and the input parameters.
      Parameters:
      speed - The speed the coordinate mover should be given.
      moveRandomly - Whether the nodes should be moved randomly.
      moveVelocity - Whether the nodes should move by velocity.
      Returns:
      DG A dynamic graph containing nodes of coordinates found on the line and initial velocities if given.
      Throws:
      IOException - Thrown if an I/O error occurs.
      NodeSuperimpositionException - Thrown if an attempt is made to superimpose nodes.

    • getNextGraph

      public StaticGraph getNextGraph() throws IOException, NodeSuperimpositionException
      Outputs a @code{StaticGraph} using the information from the next line.
      Returns:
      g A StaticGraph with nodes of coordinates given on the line.
      Throws:
      IOException - Thrown if an I/O error occurs.
      NodeSuperimpositionException - Thrown if an attempt is made to superimpose nodes.
